import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='pressure', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['pressure'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['pressure'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of atmospheric pressure in Seattle in 2010?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temperature', data=data)
    plt.axhline(data['temperature'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Average: {data['temperature'].mean():.2f}°C")
    plt.title("What is the average temperature in Seattle in 2010?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Date")
    plt.ylabel("Temperature (°C)")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wind', kde=True, color='blue', bins=25)
    median_wind = data['wind'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_wind, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_wind:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['hour'] = data['date'].dt.hour

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='hour', y='temperature', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the average temperature during different times of the day in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Hour of the Day')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature (°C)')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
